components.label: 2. Is this a Home based business?
2.a Will you be receiving clients at your residence?
2.b How many clients on average do you receive per day?

components.html: Home Occupation refers to the making, servicing, or repairing goods and the provision of services for hire from a residence. To qualify for a Home Based Business Licence the applicant must reside at the location they are applying for, be the only person engaged in the business and comply with the Home Occupation Bylaw No.84-44 Schedule D Zoning Regulation Bylaw No.80
components.label: Content
3. Do you need Inter-Municipal Licence?
components.tooltip: This will allow you to work within all 13 municipal boundaries

components.html: Businesses in a variety of mobile trades (e.g. caterers, contractors, towing services) can purchase a business licence that is honoured throughout Greater Victoria. Applicants must purchase this licence from the municipality in which their business office is located, either your home or a commercial location.
